[1] Virginia (Lynchburg)
Date: Mon 24 Feb 2014
Source: WSET [edited]
http://www.wset.com/story/24808757/whooping-cough-cases-increasing


More and more cases of whooping cough are turning up in the Lynchburg area. Just Monday morning, 24 Feb 2014, a local school put up a sign warning that a parent of a child that attends came down with the illness. The Lynchburg Health Department says they have seen an outbreak of pertussis, or whooping cough, since November 2013. There are cases in every age group from infants to the elderly, but officials say more often than not it is adults that spread the disease. "We've had more cases than expected in this area," said District
Epidemiologist Haley Phillips Evans.

Health experts say it's not necessarily kids that spread the disease. "Half of the kids that get whooping cough an adult brings them the illness," said Dr Thomas Eppes.

[Byline: Katie Brooke]

